# Multi-level snapshot merge

Canonical implementation: [`mergeSnapshot.ts`](extension/src/store/mergeSnapshot.ts), [`snapshotHierarchy.ts`](extension/src/pipeline/snapshotHierarchy.ts).

## Storage layout

```
merges/<projectSlug>/
  snapshot-manifest.json     # hierarchy index
  snapshots/l1-0001.json     # L1 leaf snapshots
  snapshots/l2-0001.json     # promoted groups
  merge-snapshot.json        # root virtual session (backward-compatible read path)
```

[`SnapshotManifest`](extension/src/store/storeTypes.ts): `topLevelIds`, `sessionToLeafId`, `nodes[]`.

## Merge contract

| Stage | M-merge LLM input | M3 trie input |
|-------|-------------------|---------------|
| **L1 leaf** | **本批真实 sessions only** (full, ≤ batch size) | **跳过** |
| **L2+ promotion** | **5 个同级 snapshot virtual sessions** (full) | **跳过** |
| **Root** | **所有 topLevel snapshot nodes** (full if >1) | **全库真实 SessionRecords** |

Entry: [`runBatchSnapshotPipeline`](extension/src/pipeline/snapshotHierarchy.ts) → [`runLeafSnapshotMerge`](extension/src/pipeline/snapshotHierarchy.ts) → [`promoteAllLevels`](extension/src/pipeline/snapshotHierarchy.ts) → [`rebuildProjectRoot`](extension/src/pipeline/snapshotHierarchy.ts).

### Session update cascade

[`refreshSnapshotForSession`](extension/src/pipeline/snapshotHierarchy.ts): rebuild L1 for `sessionToLeafId` → rebuild parent chain → promote → root + M3.

## Forbidden

- **Cumulative delta**: rewriting one project snapshot with `[old snapshot + batch]` across batches.
- **Wide M-merge**: all N library sessions in one LLM call (except root M3 uses all N for path snapping only — no LLM).
- **Periodic full reconcile** (`batchNo % N`, `mergeFullReconcileEvery` as full trigger).
- **Silent rollback** on validation failure — invalid LLM JSON **throws** ([`dev-fail-loud.mdc`](dev-fail-loud.mdc)).

## Deprecated semantics

- `batchNo` driving delta vs full in [`shouldFullReconcile`](extension/src/pipeline/deltaMergePipeline.ts) — kept for tests only.
- Single cumulative `merge-snapshot.json` rewritten each batch with all session ids.
- `library.mergeMode` / `mergeFullReconcileEvery` — legacy labels; hierarchy always uses bounded full merges per level.

## Imperfect merges OK

Accept imperfect structure when LLM JSON **passed validation**. Do not rollback sibling snapshots on batch 2+ style failures — abort the failing level write only.
